From: Steven Rostedt <srostedt@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Sep 2008 17:00:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Subject: Change bug_on for atomic to pagefault_disabled.
 The lockless page changes decoupled the pagefault disabled
 from preempt count. The bug_on in filemap.c is now not correct.
 This patch uses the proper check.

Signed-off-by: Steven Rostedt <srostedt@redhat.com>
---
 mm/filemap.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/filemap.c b/mm/filemap.c
index 0c45031..1fc034a 100644
--- a/mm/filemap.c
+++ b/mm/filemap.c
@@ -1817,7 +1817,7 @@ size_t iov_iter_copy_from_user_atomic(struct page *page,
 	size_t copied;
 
 #ifndef CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT
-	BUG_ON(!in_atomic());
+	BUG_ON(!current->pagefault_disabled);
 #endif
 	kaddr = kmap_atomic(page, KM_USER0);
 	if (likely(i->nr_segs == 1)) {
